Battle of North Falador was the battle in year 163 of 5th age between the Falador [[White Knights]] and the [[Kinshra]].{{CiteText|text= Varrock Museum#2nd_floor3rd_floor_display_cases{{!}}Display case 26|name = case|quote=Year 163, 5th Age - The White Knights declared that the Black knights were no longer to have any political power within Asgarnia. Lord Daquarius of the Kinshra immediately responds by declaring his Black Knights as being at a state of war with Falador. The two sides engaged in a big battle to the north of Falador.}}

The battle was result of power revolution in [[Falador]] when [[King Vallance]], then ruler of [[Asgarnia]], became ill.{{CiteText|text= Varrock Museum#2nd_floor3rd_floor_display_cases{{!}}Display case 26|quote=The old king of Asgarnia, King Vallance, falls very ill. The White Knights took advantage of this and began to take control of Falador and Asgarnia for themselves.}} The White Knights used this opportunity to take over Falador and declared that the Black Knights wouldn't have any political power within Asgarnia. [[Lord Daquarius]] of the Kinshra immediately declared  a state of war with Falador.{{NamedRef|case}}

The battle itself was fought north of Falador, between Falador and the Black knight fortress. Both sides were evenly matched, and ultimately both armies retreated to their respective fortresses in order to rebuild their strength and eventually crush the other side once and for all.{{CiteText|text= Varrock Museum#2nd_floor3rd_floor_display_cases{{!}}Display case 26|quote=however, both sides were fairly evenly matched, and retreated to their fortresses to build up their forces and devise plans to crush the other, once and for all.}}

